ut whether we need a test run. I’m looking into the necessary setup for running with the system property '-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow' for Netty 4.2.x on Java 25. It looks like the existing build applies to 5.0.0, and I'm not sure about the requirements for 5.0.1. I’ll also consider dependencies and ensure the proper configuration for the web client with Vert.x.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating test setup**\\n\\nI’m considering if the existing tests pass and whether Jackson databind is necessary. I’ll check the POM for resolved artifacts and see if there are optional HTTP2 alpn native dependencies. It seems like Netty native transports might not be needed for significant coverage. Also, I should advise on configuring the environment and system properties for test setup. It looks like I need to ensure the runtime JVM arguments are set appropriately for Java 25 native runs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Identifying risks in testing**\\n\\nI need to consider the potential risks if the tests only exercise loopback HTTP without involving Docker. This limitation could affect how accurately the tests represent real-world scenarios. I’m curious if this approach could lead to missing issues that might arise in a fully deployed environment. I should explore if there are alternative testing strategies that could provide a more comprehensive evaluation while still keeping things efficient. It will be interesting to see how I can address this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 resolves to Vert.x Core 5.0.1 and Netty 4.2.2.Final, same Netty 4.2.x line as the existing 5.0.0 test, which already requires Java 25 native-run system properties. No extra Maven dependency or Docker service appears necessary for meaningful coverage; loopback Vert.x HTTP server/client tests are sufficient.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image run coverage on JDK 25, configure the generated test/native runtime with `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`, extending the existing 5.0.0 Netty 4.2.x workaround to 5.0.1. Use in-process Vert.x `HttpServer`/`WebClient` loopback tests for requests, JSON/body codecs, forms, multipart upload, redirects, cookies/session, and caching; no external service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failure is in native-image run, so local Gradle/native-image verification remains authoritative.\",\n    \"If generated tests add HTTPS/HTTP2, DNS, proxy, or native transport coverage, additional Netty/JDK behavior may surface, but this is not required for normal Web Client coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_093bd519edc1e736016a4012e03f388195ba2101cc810a9f50\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2759, "output": 821, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20988, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782584019439, "responseId": "resp_093bd519edc1e736016a4012d3cedc81958139d1ad2332b5bf"}, "toolResults": []}
